name: Spice Goa

reviews.review_text: In a quest to search for the best Goan fish thali, we landed here on a weekend during lunch hours and oh boy, it was a painful wait of an hour in the scorching heat. Even after we had booked a table for 8 the previous night through Easy Diner platform, the restaurant denied and did not honour our booking because of an issue between them and the Easy Diner platform. We were seated on the top deck after an hour and we ordered a few Fish Thalis, King Fish masala fry, egg fried rice, chicken lollipops, Goan veg platter and veg biryani and a few drinks to go with it. As soon as the thali arrived, we started belting and collectively decided that this was the best Goan Fish thali out of all the thalis we had during our 6-day trip to Goa. The prawns curry, the boneless fish fry, the sides to go with it were all very tasty and fulfilling. Even the barfi on the plate was too good. Chicken lollipops and egg fried rice were great too. King Fish masala fry was a bit sour to our taste and was not liked by everyone. The server did give us a heads up about it before we ordered it, so it's all good. The only disappointment was the Goan veg platter. Paying a premium for such less veg sides was not a good plan and the items did not taste very well either. Overall, it was a great experience devouring Goan fish thali and other seafood and chicken items here. A worthy visit and I highly recommend this place for other tourists/travellers. The restrooms were neat and clean and the sinks were kept well and tidy too. The restaurant has won a lot of awards and accolades and the same has been stuck on the wall and one can witness it while going to the top deck. The only nitpicking here i would do is the cramped space and how tiny the restaurant and the waiting area is. It is a very cramped space and a 6 feet human has to bend and watch their head on the top deck while walking around. Even the crowd gets too busy and takes away the ambience of having good food. The waiting area is overfilled during peak lunch hours and one has to stay back in the heat while their family and/or friends wait in the car with the comfort of air conditioning until they get a table confirmation.

Great food, Service and atmosphere is good too.
You can try goan food and north Indian as well.

Overhyped restaurant. The cramped & noisy ambience is a telltale of the obnoxious & rude service being provided by the outlet. We found no tissues on the table,no water was offered,no finger bowls & a general apathy towards customers. The food at best was decent. Nothing to match the hype. Plenty of brilliant restaurants in Goa. Makes no sense visiting this restaurant. Not recommended.

description:
### Welcome to Spice Goa: An Authentic Culinary Experience in Assonora

Nestled in the heart of Assonora, Goa, **Spice Goa** successfully captivates visitors with an impressive rating of **4.4** from over **5,300 reviews**. This beloved establishment is frequently tagged with words like **Goan (361)**, **Thali (209)**, **Serradura (68)**, and **Banana Leaf (55)**, showcasing its strong focus on regional cuisine and traditional dining styles. The restaurant is particularly celebrated for its **Goan fish thali**, making it a must-visit for anyone seeking an authentic taste of Goa.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Spice Goa, guests are greeted by a cozy yet cramped space that may feel bustling, especially during peak hours. The depiction of the top deck in recent photos shows a modest design with rustic elements, accented by warm lighting and vibrant colors typical of Goan culture. However, several reviews point out that the limited space can lead to a noisy atmosphere that sometimes detracts from the dining experience. Patrons may have to navigate low ceilings and a crowded waiting area, which, on a particularly busy day, can overwhelm one‚Äôs patience, especially in the Goa heat.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The highlight of the menu is undeniably the **Goan Fish Thali**‚Äîa visual and culinary feast that has garnered rave reviews. One enthusiastic diner shared their experience of savoring the thali during a recent visit, describing the **prawns curry** and **boneless fish fry** as exceptional. Accompanying sides, including a delectable **barfi**, further elevate the meal, although some dishes like the **King Fish masala fry** received mixed feedback for their tartness, offering a balance of flavors for discerning palates. Vegetarian options like the **Goan veg platter** have evoked some criticisms for their portioning and taste, but the abundant seafood and chicken dishes mostly earn high praise, making it a rich choice for meat lovers.  

Moreover, the presentation and authenticity of returning dishes served on traditional banana leaves exemplify a commitment to gastronomic tradition that patrons appreciate. For those craving diversity, the menu also offers a tantalizing selection of **North Indian food**‚Äîanother point of mention from satisfied customers.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer service at Spice Goa has garnered mixed reviews. Some diners laud the genuine friendliness of the staff, while others expressed frustration over inefficient service during peak hours, with inconsistent attentiveness highlighted by one review citing a lack of basic table necessities such as tissues and finger bowls. However, it's worth noting that staff members did make efforts to recommend dishes wisely, even cautioning about the sourness of certain items. Reservation handling has also raised issues, with one diner detailing a frustrating experience regarding a previously made booking that was not honored.

### Popularity & Reviews

Despite the criticisms, it appears **Spice Goa** enjoys robust popularity, which speaks volumes to its culinary offerings. Many reviews collectively sing praises of the **thali meals**, solidifying its reputation as a go-to spot for authentic Goan cuisine. Social media buzz surrounding the restaurant reveals a loyal customer base eager to recommend it to tourists, alongside awards and accolades displayed on the restaurant walls, hinting at its established recognition in the local dining scene.

### Visual Highlights

The atmosphere and menu at Spice Goa shine through beautifully in the customer-provided images. The vibrant plates of the fish thali reveal a colorful array of curries and garnishes, emphasizing the restaurant's rich flavors and visual appeal. The casual yet warm decor is notable even in images, contributing to the restaurant's character, although potential visitors should be aware of the busy environment depicted in the photos.

In conclusion, **Spice Goa** beckons culinary adventurers with its promise of authentic Goan flavors and a vibrant atmosphere. Visitors are encouraged to embrace the restaurant's chaotic charm, savor its exquisite fish thali, and perhaps find joy in the lively dining experience that defines Goan culture.
